  "prompt": "What universities does Thor Industries recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Thor Industries, a leading manufacturer of recreational vehicles (RVs), collaborates with various universities and technical colleges to recruit new graduates. While specific partnerships can vary, they generally focus on institutions with strong engineering, business, supply chain, and manufacturing programs. Some of the universities and colleges they have recruited from in the past include:\n\n1. **Purdue University** - Engineering, Business, and Supply Chain Management.\n2. **Iowa State University** - Engineering, Business, and Agricultural Systems Technology.\n3. **University of Notre Dame** - Business, Engineering, and Operations Management.\n4. **Indiana University** - Business, Supply Chain Management, and Marketing.\n5. **Ball State University** - Business, Operations Management, and Marketing.\n6. **Western Michigan University** - Engineering, Business, and Supply Chain Management.\n7. **Trine University** - Engineering and Business.\n8. **Ivy Tech Community College** - Skilled Trades, Manufacturing, and Engineering Technology.\n\n### Majors Thor Industries Typically Looks For:\n- **Engineering**: Mechanical Engineering, Industrial Engineering, Electrical Engineering, and Manufacturing Engineering.\n- **Business**: Supply Chain Management, Operations Management, Marketing, Finance, and Human Resources.\n- **Skilled Trades and Technical Programs**: Welding, CNC Machining, and Manufacturing Technology.\n- **Information Technology**: IT, Data Analytics, and Software Development.\n\nThor Industries also participates in career fairs, on-campus recruiting events, and internship programs to connect with students and recent graduates. For the most accurate and updated information, it\u2019s best to check their official [careers page](https://www.thorindustries.com/careers) or contact their recruitment team directly.",
